<descript>
<abstract>New York City Predicted Particulate Matter 2.5 Microns Surface, 2009 is a raster dataset representing estimated levels of fine particulate matter (less than 2.5 microns) in New York City in 2009. The resolution is approximately 300 meters and the units are parts per billion.  This dataset was generated for the air pollution rasters dataset on NYC Open Data at https://data.cityofnewyork.us/Environment/NYCCAS-Air-Pollution-Rasters/q68s-8qxv/about_data in May of 2026.  Columbia Libraries has made this available in GeoTIFF format in State Plane Coordinates.  Original documentation can be found in the full download package.  </abstract>
